        "quiries_LHCfix": {
          "type": "quiries",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Consent and acknowledgement",
            "question": "Q10: Please confirm that you are aware of the following",
            "paragraph_list_text": "<p>a) Avoid using cosmetic nail varnish for the duration of treatment<br/>b) Keep nails trimmed short and filed down.<br/>c) Avoid sharing toenail clippers with family members.<br/>d) Wear well-fitting non-occlusive shoes, without high heels or narrow toes. Consider replacing old footwear which could be contaminated with fungal spores.<br/>e) Wear cotton, absorbent socks.<br/>f) Maintain good foot hygiene<br/>g) Wear protective footwear when using communal bathing places, locker rooms, and gymnasiums, to avoid re-exposure.<br/>h) Avoid prolonged or frequent exposure to warm, damp conditions if possible.<br/>i) Avoid trauma to the nails if<br/>possible.<br/>j) Seek medical attention if condition worsens while using amorolfine nail lacquer or no improvement of nails after a period of 3 months treatment</p>",
